{"/service/ndnp/ncu/batch_ncu_lagarde_ver02/data/sn99061530/00332892605/1958060601/1165.xml":{"full_text":"FRIDAY, JUNE 6, 1958\nCLASSIFIED\n.ADVERTISING.\nADVERTISING IN THESE COLUMNS COSTS THREE CENTS PER\nWORD, FIRST INSERTION: ALL INSERTIONS AFTER FIRST, TWO\nCENTS PER WORD. MINIMUM CHARGE IS 50 CENTS. IF YOU\nWANT TO BUY, RENT, SELL, SWAP, GET A JOB, HIRE HELP.\nFIND SOMETHING LOST, THE CLASSIFIEDS OFFER AN EFFEC\nTIVE AND ECONOMICAL MEDIUM.\nVisit ANDERSON\u2019S SUPER\nMARKET-BEACH STORE at\ntwo mile post. Vacation headquar\nters. Open year \u2019round. Write\nBILL ANDERSON\u2019S RENTAL\nAGENCY, KITTY HAWK, reser\nvations, oceanfront housekeeping\ncottages. T-4-8-tfc\nHOME IMPROVEMENTS\u2014Roof\ning, siding, garages built, rooms\nadded, baths installed complete,\nbrick and cement work, painting\n\u2022r anything else you want to im\nprove your home. Pay nothing\ndown, 36 months to pay. See\nCharles Haskett or phone 5704\nElizabeth City. T-8-9-tfc\nOFFICE SUPPLIES, PRINTING\norders for printing of all kinds\nfilled promptly. We print forms,\nblanks, letterheads, statements, en\nvelopes. Order from your Pilot and\nHerald Agent, or Times Printing\nCo., Manteo, N. C. We carry book\nkeeping supplies, and some office\nfurniture.\nINDEPENDENT insurance agen\ncies can and will \u201cserve you\nfirst.\u201d Contact us for yours now.\nHugh Fortescue, Washington.\nTPH-8-29-tfc\nCAMELLIAS, azaleas, hollies, va\nriety of evergreen plants 1.00\nup; Pyracantha (red berried) 1.00;\nnice flowering trees and shrubs;\nJuniper, Cypress, Arborvitae; Let\nus help you to make your home\nmore beautiful. Roanoke Island\nGardens, Manteo, N. C. Corner\nMother Vineyard Rd. T-l-24-tfc\nFOR SALE. Gas space heater, $lO.\nGas 2 Burner Stove, $lO. Gas 4\nburner stove and oven, S2O. Com\nplete beds, double and single, $lO\nChina cabinet, $lO. Frigidaire,\n$lO. Day bed, $lO. Call Mrs.\nO\u2019Neat, Manteo iB7 W-l.\nT-5-30-3tp\nHELP WANTED, male: Man to\nsell Nationally Advertised Wat\nkins products in Hyde County.\nProducts well known for 90 years.\nDealers enjoying substantial in\ncrease in come this year. Appli\ncant must have good character and\nown car. If interested write Mr.\nR. L. Rollins, P. O. Box 113, Golds\nl>oro, N. C. PH-5-29-3tc\nSEASHORE VACATIONS on Hat\nteras Island near Oregon Inlet,\nat low cost family-style boarding.\nPhone 130, Mirlo Beach Lodge, Ro\ndanthe. Write for information.\nARTIFICIAL BREEDING of your\ncows to purebred, proven stocks\nis both profitable and economical.\nThis service available to family\ncow owners, beef producers, dairy\nherds. All dairy and beef breeds\navailable. Call H. E. Clayton, Bel\nhaven WH 3-3206. P-10-4-tfc\nSAVE YOUR FLOORS and nice\ntile; use plastic and rubber cups\nander your desk and furniture legs.\nAll sizes in stock. Times Printing\nCo., Manteo, N. C.\nFor your insurance needs see\nW. R. PEARCE, Manteo, N. C.\nt All kinds of insurance\nWURLITZER SPINET Piano at\nNags Head real bargain. Custo\nmer giving up on account health.\nTake up payments on balance due\nsave us {ticking it up. E. R.\nPOOLE MUSIC COMPANY, RA\nLEIGH, N. C. T-4-25-7tc\nPETUNIAS, Salvia, 1.50 doz;\nSweet William SI.OO Doz.;\nDouble Petunias, Ageratums, Bro\nwallias, $2.00 Doz. Verbena,\nColeus, Lantana, Saltana, 25t\u2018 each;\nalso, geraniums, begonias, fuchias,\nachyranthus, ivies, foliage plants,\netc. Roanoke Island Gardens,\nPhone 210-J, Manteo, N. C.\nT-5-9-6tc\nWANTED AT ONCE\u2014Rawleigh\nDealer in Hyde and Tyrrell Coun\nties. Write Rawleigh\u2019s, Dept. NCF\n-480-R, Richmond, Va.\nPH-6-5-4tp\nWANTED \u2014Man with car between\nthe ages of 25 to 55 to handle\na Watkins Business Business in\nHyde County. Dealer willing to\ninvest 5 days a week in handling\nhis own business can make above\naverage earnings. Products Na\ntionally Advertised. Field help\nprovided. Free Insurance. Com\npany now celebrating 90th year\nin business with great dividend\ndeals. Business is permanent and\nprofitable with no layoffs for the\nman who wants to operate his\nown business with Company capi\ntal. For full particulars write to\nday to The J. R. Watkins Com\npany, P. O. Box 5071, Richmond,\nVirginia. PH-5-15-stc\nSAVE NOW. on Mattresses. We\nwill allow you $24.50 for any old\nmattress on the purchase of a new\n$51.50 Dreamer Superior. You pay\nonly $35.00 Old mattresses made\nnew. All new furniture price.\nWe deliver. Weldon Mattress Co.,\nWeldon, N. C. T-5-30-tfe\nCO2 fire extinguishers, S2O each\nor two for $35. USCG approved.\nG. G. Bonner, General Supply Co.,\nManteo. Tel. 4-W. T-11-8-tfc\nTHE OLD SEA CAPTAIN AND\nDRUMMER Book sl, postpaid.\nGet this racy book of dialogue\nfrom Cape Hatteras and the N. C.\nCoastland. Send it to your friends,\n6 copies $5 postpaid. Times Print\ning Co.. Inc., Manteo, N. C.\nGET-WELL CARDS See our\nnew assortments, just arrived, both\nserious and humorous. TIMES\nPRINTING COMPANY, Manteo.\nREAL ESTATE on Coast. If in-\nterested in buying or selling\nCoastal property of any kind, try\nthe MIRLO CO., Phone 244, Man\nteo, N. C.\nRUBBER STAMPS made to order,\nstamp pads, etc. Leave orders at\nPilot and Herald Office, in Bel\nhaven or Swan Quarter.\nARTISTS SUPPLIES. Speed ball\nsets, India ink, black drawing\nink, silver ink, white ink, drawing\npaper. TIMES PRINTING CO.,\nInc., Manteo. tc\nFOR SALE: Westinghouse table-\ntype sewing machine, SSO. Excel\nlent condition. Mrs. Shirley Jor\ndan. Call Manteo 320-J.\nT-5-23-tfc\nFOR SALE Gas refrigerator,\nfamily size. Good working con\ndition. Manteo 196. T-5-30-tfc\nLAWN MOWER REPAIRING. We\nrepair all makes of lawnmowers\nand small gasoline engines. Parts\navailable for all makes and models.\nSatisfaction guaranteed. ALEX\u2019S\nREPAIR SHOP, Wanchese. N. C.\nPhone 248-J2. T-5-2-tfc\nBOAT FOR SALE: 14-ft. Scotch\nCraft boat, 16 hp Scott Atwater\nmotor and Cox Trailer. Boat newly\npainted and fibre-glassed. $425\ncomplete. Tel. Nags Head 2502 or\ncan be seen at Britt\u2019s Antique\nShop, Nags Head. T-6-6-2tc\nHOUSE FOR RENT: three bed\nrooms, bath, unfurnished. Con\ntact C. B. Parker, Manteo. Tel.\n78-J. T-6-6-2tp\nTYPEWRITERS, rebuilt and re-\nconditioned, sold at less than\nmail order prices. All makes in\nstock. The Pilot and Herald, Bel\nhaven, N. C. or Times Printing Co.,\nManteo.\nFOR SALE: Norge electric refrig\nerator, 60 lb. freezer chest.\nEdna J. Etheridge. Call Nags\nHead 8151. T-6-6-2tc\nOUTBOARD LAKE Evinrude Mo-\ntor, \u201957, 2-gas-tank. battery for\nsale. Belton Burrus, Manteo.\nT-6-6-lt\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nNotice is hereby given that the\npartnership heretofore existing\nwherein Dan C. Morrill and Char\nlotte S. Morrill were partners trad\ning and doing business under the\nfirm name of Island Photo Service,\nin the Town of Manteo, in the\nCounty of Dare, North Carolina,\nhas this day been dissolved by\nmutual consent of the partners.\nThis 16th day of May, 1958.\n/s/ DAN C. MORRILL\nZs/ CHARLOTTE S. MORRILL\nSeagrams\nGoma\nL\u2014M7-J\n7 I***!*\n\nWHOVJG ftOtf.46% SMUYt.\nI \u2022-nr-\nNOTICE\nNORTH CAROLINA\nDARE COUNTY\nThe undersigned having duly\nqualified as the administrator of\nthe Estate of Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, late of the above named\ncounty and state, all persons hav\ning claims of whatsoever nature\nagainst the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby notified to\nexhibit the said claim or claims to\nthe undersigned on or before the\n2nd day of May, 1959, or this\nnotice will be pleaded in bar of\ntheir recovery. All persons indebt\ned to the said Melton V. Hooper,\ndeceased, are hereby requested to\npay the said indebtedness to the\nundersigned immediately.\nThis the 2nd day of May, 1958.\nFLOYD L. HOOPER\nAdministrator\nT-5-2-6tc\nNOTICE OF SALE\nSTATE OF NORTH CAROLINA\nCOUNTY OF DARE\nUnder and by virtue of the\npower of sale contained in a cer\ntain deed of trust executed by El\nmer V. Midgett and Evelyn Mid\ngett, his wife, dated the 20th day of\nMarch, 1956 and recorded in Book\nNo. 66 on page 252 in the \"office\nof the Register of Deeds, Dare\nCounty, North Carolina, default\nhaving been made in the payment\nof the indebtedness thereby secur\ned and the said deed of trust being\nby its terms subject to trustee\u2019s\nforeclosure sale, the undersigned\ntrustee will offer for sale at pub\nlic auction to highest bidder for\ncash at the Courthouse door, Man\nteo, N. C.. being sold at 12 o\u2019clock i\nnoon on the 20 day of June, 1958,\nthe following described property:\nA parcel of land described as\nParcel B of tract No. six in that\ncertain Report of Commissioners\nin a partition proceeding dated\nJune 22, 1951, and duly recorded\nin Book 41, page 209, Office of\nthe Register of Deeds, Dare\nCounty, North Carolina, map or\nplat showing said parcel record\ned with the proceedings. Said\nportion of Parcel B. being de\nscribed as:\nBeginning at a stake or other\nmarker, said beginning point be\ning South 76 degrees 30 minutes\nEast a distance of 400 feet from\nan iron axel located on the east\nern margin of the right-of-way\nof that highway known as the\nHatteras Highway which extends\nfrom Oregon Inlet to the village\nof Hatteras; said iron axel here\nin referred to as a reference\npoint being in the south line of\nParcel B of Tract No. 6, as said\nsouth line intersects with the\naforesaid right-ofway, same be\ning shown on the map or plat\nhereinabove mentioned; and run\nning thence from said beginning\npoint in a northerly direction and\nparallel with aforesaid highway\nright-of-way a distance of 68.1\nfeet to a stake or other marker;\nand running thence South 76\ndegrees 30 minutes East along\nthe northern line of the Parcel\nB of Tract No. 6 as shown on\naforesaid map a distance of 1900\nfeet more or less to the high\nwater mark of the Atlantic\nOcean; and \"thence running in a\nsoutherly direction along the\nhighwater mark of the Atlantic\nOcean a distance of 68.1 feet;\nand thence running North 76\ndegrees 30 minutes West along\nthe southern line of Parcel B of\nTract No. 6 as shown on afore\nsaid map a distance of 1900 feet\nmore or less to the stake or\nother marker at the place of\nbeginning.\nAnd being the portion of Par\ncel B -of Tract No. 6 which lies\nbetween a line parallel with and\n400 feet distance from the afore\nsaid highway right-of-wav, and\nthe highwater mark of the At\nlantic Ocean.\nTerms of sale: Cash, or such\nother terms as the Trustee may\ndeed expedient.\nThe property is to be sold as\nis, where is, without warranty of\nany kind, and subject to taxes\nand/or assessments, if any.\nPurchaser will not be allowed\nto sever or remove any of the\nsaid property or to take possession\nthereof without first complying\nwith the bid.\nDated this 16 dav of May, 1958.\nCLARENCE P. MOORE, Trustee\nT-5-23-4tc\nTHE COASTLAND TIMES, MANTEO, N. C.\nKITTY HAWK PERSONALS\nServices were held at Primitive\nBaptist Church on the week end.\nElder George G. Trevathian,\nspeaker. Visitors were Elders S.\nR. Boykin and W. C. Trevathian.\nMr. and Mrs. Paul Pruitt and\ntwo children are visiting Mr. and\nMrs. Leon Perry. Mr. Pruitt, with\nthe U. S. Air Force has been sev\neral years in Texas and is being\ntransferred from Amarilla, Texas\nto College Park, Md., as of July\nIst.\nRoy Beacham, Jr., U. S. C. G. C.\nChincoteague is on a trip to Ar\ngentia for about one month.\nMr. and Mrs. Sherwood Perry,\nArlington, Va., and son, Creig and\nhis wife, spent the week end at\ntheir .beach cottage.\nThomas M. Dowdy, U. S. C. G.\nNantucket Lightship, Boston, is\nhome for two weeks.\nLeslie R. Henley, U. S. C. G. C.\nMadrona, Norfolk, Va., is in Balti\nmore, Curtis Bay yard for ship\noverhaul and repairs.\nJack Finn, U. S. C. G. Elizabeth\nCity Sta. was home a few days.\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of Naomi D.\nWescott of Manteo, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said Naomi D. Wes\ncott to present them to the under\nsigned within one year from date\nof this notice or same will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 6th dav t>f May, 1958.\nBROCKIIE DANIELS\nManteo, N. C.\n-5-16-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of John Alford\nFarrow of Manteo, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said John Alford\nFarrow to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will be\npleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease 'make immediate payment.\nThis the sth dav of May, 1958.\nALICE F. MEEKINS\nAvon, N. C.\n_ T-5-9-6tc\nADMINISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Executors\nof the Estate of Guy H. Lennon,\nof Dare County, North Carolina,\nthis is to notify all persons hav\ning claims against the Estate of\nsaid Guy H. Lennon, to present\nthem to the undersigned within\none year from the date of this\nnotice, or the same will be pleaded\nin bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said\nEstate please make immediate\npayment to the undersigned.\nThis 4th day of June, 1958\nR. B. LENNON\nW. E. LENNON, M. D.\nExecutors\nMcCown McCown, Attorneys\nManteo, N. C.\nTHANK YOU, VOTERS\nAt this time I wish to thank each and every\nperson of Dare County who supported me in any\nway at the Democratic Primary election. I also\nwish to thank each individual who helped in any\nway, by encouragement, by work or friendship.\nAgain, I give my sincere appreciation and\nthanks. X\nHORACE B. HOOPER\nStumpy Point, N. C.\n4\nTO THE CITIZENS\nOF DARE COUNTY\nThank you, most sincerely, for your vote of confidence\nas expressed in the May 31st Primary.\nJ t\nAs promised, I will serve to the best of my ability as\nyour Commissioner from Hatteras Township; without being\ninfluenced by any particular individual or group, or show\nany partiality to any special section.\nIn the near future, I will visit each Township and\npersonnally express my appreciation, and also to become\nbetter acquainted with the people and their wishes.\n\nRespectfully,\nGEORGE R. FULLER, JR.\nEVERYDAY\nRELIGION\nBy Rev. Robert W. Turner\nEvery truly religious person is\nvitally interested in what we\nloosely call \u201cpolitics.\u201d We are in\nterested because this concerns the\ngoverning of the community in\nwhich we, as citizens, live and we\nknow that how it is governed will\naffect the welfare of each individ\nual person for good or ill.\n\u201cPoliticians\u201d are actually the\n\u2018men of state\u2019 who are entrusted\nby the people of the state with the\naffairs of government. Once elect\ned by the people, through the\ndemocratic process of a free public\nvote, the officer of government\nrepresents each and every person\nin the community, regardless of\nhis own ideas or \u201cparty'\u2019 affilia\ntions. Each office carries with it\ncertain powers and elected repre\nsentatives must remember con\nstantly their obligation to all the\npeople and to Almighty God,\nsince abuse and mis-use of power\nis a temptation common to all men.\nW recognize that each public\noffice is, therefore, a solemn re\nsponsibility and is not to be en\ntered into lightly or selfishly, but\nin the reverence of Almighty God\nwhose children the people are and\nover whom He watches.\nEach citizen of the community,\nin turn, is responsible for sup\nporting the elected representative\nin \u201cevery good work\u201d undertaken\nfor community betterment of what\never the nature may be and will\nassist with a good will towards\nthis end.\nThe Church people of the com\nmunity will certainly have the pub\nlic officers constantly in their\nprayers, both public and private,\nand will assist in promoting .that\npeace which is the \u201cfruit of right\neousness.\u201d\nThe time is past for the people\nto make vain and empty jokes\nabout the persons whom they\nelect to responsible positions or to\nplace the blame for failures on\nthe \u201cother party.\u201d Is not this to be\nand act irresponsible ourselves?\nAnd why should a leaking pot call\nthe kettle black Rather let us,\nindividually and corporately,\npledge ourselves to think, study,\nwork and pray with those whom\nwe elect toward the common goal\nfor which they are elected. Praise\nthe Lord and pass by the ammuni\ntion of destructive criticism\u2014but\nkeep your eye on the power keg.\nFor your Paint and Supplies\nAlways Stop at\nFEARINGS. INC.\nWHY? We offer a complete line\nTHANKS TO THE VOTERS\nI wish to take this opportunity\nto thank all the voters in every\nDare County District, who gave\nme their support, for the office of\nCoroner on May 31, 1958.\nJAMES M. VANNOTE\nBUS SCHEDULE\nBETWEEN MANTEO\nAND HATTERAS\nEffective April 1, 1958\nNORTHBOUND\nLv. Hatteras 9:00 A.M.\nAr. Manteo 11:45 A.M.\nSOUTHBOUND\nLv. Manteo 2:45 P.M.\nAr. Hatteras 5:45 P.M.\nCHARTERED TRIPS\nHATTERAS-MANTEO\nBUS LINE\nPhone 104 Hatteras, N. C.\nADMINISTRATOR S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Administra\ntrix of the estate of Dennett Hen\nry Ransom of Frisco, Dare County,\nNorth Carolina, this is to notify\nall persons having claims against\nthe estate of said Dennett Henry\nRansom to present them to the\nundersigned within one year from\ndate of this notice or same will\nbe pleaded in bar of their recovery.\nAll persons indebted to said estate\nplease make immediate payment.\nThis the 28th day of April, 1958.\nELLA MAY RANSOM\nFrisco, N. C.\nT-5-2-6tc\nSTATEMENT BY DAVID STICK\nI take this opportunity to express my appreciation to\nthe many voters who supported me in the recent primary\nelection, and to my opponent, Hallett Perry, for the fair\nmanner in which he conducted his campaign.\nDavid Stick\nNOTICE TO BIDDERS\nFOR THE REMOVAL OF\nGARBAGE AND TRASH\nON THE DARE BEACHES\nSealed bids will be received in the office of the\nRegister of Deeds, as Clerk to the Board of County Com\nmissioners of Dare County, until 12:00 o'clock Noon on\nJune 17, 1958 for the removal of all garbage and house\nhold trash, exclusive of construction materials, from the\nportion of the Dare Beaches described hereinafter for the\nperiod beginning July I, 1958 and terminating June 30,\n1959, in accordance with the following schedule:\nCollections are to be made once each day, except\nSundays, during the period beginning July I, 1958\nthrough September 30, 1958 inclusive, and twice each\nweek during the period from October I, 1958 to and in\ncluding the 15th day of May, 1959, and three times each\nweek during the period from the 16th day of May, 1959\nto and including the 31st day of May, 1959, and once each\nday, except Sundays, for the period from June I, 1959\nthrough June 30, 1959 inclusive.\nThe general territory and area from which the afore\nsaid household trash and garbage shall be removed in\ncludes all houses, hotels, places of business and restaurants\nlying adjacent to and in the vicinity of and along that\nsection of the present U. S. Highway No. 158 extending\nfrom the East end of the Currituck Sound Bridge to the\nEast end of the Roanoke Sound Bridge, the entire South\nern Shores road or street leading North from U. S. High\nway No. 158, including the area or subdivision in S'outhern\nShores known as Crescent Village, that portion of the\nOregon Inlet road leading South from the aforesaid High\nway No. 158 lying North of the Cape Hatteras National\nSeashore Recreational Area's North line, that portion of\nthe Beach known as the Southside at Nags Head and the\npaved road leading thereto, all of the area and subdivi\nsion known as Avalon Beach or Shores, and on both sides\nof any paved or stabilized and all weather road or street\nleading from U. S. Highway No. 158 or U. S. Highway\nNo. 64 now in being, upon which houses have been\nconstructed, for a distance not in excess of one-half mile.\nThe contractor will be required to provide a dumping\nground or other disposal area for the aforesaid trash and\ngarbage which shall not be in violation of any health or\nother laws. The contractor will likewise be required to\nfurnish trucks or other disposal units or equipment which\nare covered and enclosed, and which prevents seepage or\nleakage of wet garbage.\nEach bid or proposal shall be accompanied by a\ncash deposit or a certified check or bank draft made\nEayable to the order of Dare County drawn on some\nank or trust company insured by the Federal Deposit\nInsurance Corporation in an amount equal to not less\nthan five percent of the proposal or bid. No proposal\nor bid shall be accepted or considered by the said Board\nunless at the time of its filing the same shall be accom\npanied by said deposit or check as aforesaid. This deposit\nshall be retained by Dare County if the bidder who is\naccepted and to whom the contract is awarded fails to\nexecute the contract for the aforesaid removal of garbage\nand household trash on or before the 26th day of June,\n1958, and fails to give the performance bond as provided\nhereinafter.\nThe successful bidder will be required to give a per\nformance bond for 100 percent of the contract price\nguaranteeing the faithful performance of his contract.\nSaid bond to be executed by a surety company licensed\nunder the laws of the State of North Carolina to execute\nsuch a bond.\nThe right to reject any and all bids and proposals\nfor any reason whatsoever is hereby reserved.\nFurther information concerning the bids and a copy\nof the contract which the accepted bidder will be .required\nto enter into may be had at the office of the Register of\nDeeds of Dare County, North Carolina.\nThis the 4th day of June, 1958.\nMELVIN R. DANIELS, CLERK TO THE BOARD OF\nCOUNTY COMMISSIONERS OF DARE COUNTY. N. C.\nROBERT LEE MIDGETT\nTHANKS VOTERS OF\nDARE COUNTY\nI am grateful to all those people\ni who encouraged me by their vote\nand support in the Democratic\nprimary on Saturday.\nIt was a completely new experi\nence to me, and from it I have\nlearned a great deal, and your\nmany courtesies as I went among\nthe people, encourage me to strive\nfor greater performance of my\nduty as a Democrat and as a citi\nzen of Dare County.\nWhen I can be of service to the\nparty or the county, I trust I will\nbe called upon, and I will be loyal,\nand helpful in every way possible.\nSincerely yours,\nROBERT LEE MIDGETT\nManteo, N. C.\nA DM INISTRATOR\u2019S NOTICE\nHaving qualified as Executor of\nthe estate of Daisy 11. Midgett of\nNags Head, Dare County, North\nCarolina, this is to notify all per\nsons having claims against the\nestate of said Daisy H. Midgett,\nto present them to the undersigned\nwithin one year from date of this\nnotice or same will be pleaded in\nbar of their recovery. All persons\nindebted to said estate please make\nimmediate payment.\nThis the 3rd day of May, 1958.\nCORNELIUS P. MIDGETT\nNags Head, N. C.\nWorth and Horner, Attorney.\nT-5-9-6tc\nPAGE SEVEN","height":"25688","width":"18217"}}
